  "prompt": "What are the best romantic comedy movies?",
  "response": "There have been many beloved romantic comedies over the years, and the \"best\" can vary depending on personal taste. However, here are some widely acclaimed romantic comedies that have enjoyed enduring popularity:\n\n1. **When Harry Met Sally... (1989)** - Directed by Rob Reiner and written by Nora Ephron, this film stars Billy Crystal and Meg Ryan and explores whether men and women can just be friends.\n\n2. **Pretty Woman (1990)** - This film stars Julia Roberts and Richard Gere in a modern-day fairy tale about a Hollywood hooker and a wealthy businessman.\n\n3. **10 Things I Hate About You (1999)** - A teen romantic comedy inspired by Shakespeare's \"The Taming of the Shrew,\" it stars Heath Ledger and Julia Stiles.\n\n4. **Bridget Jones's Diary (2001)** - Based on the novel by Helen Fielding, this movie stars Ren\u00e9e Zellweger, Hugh Grant, and Colin Firth, portraying the humorous and relatable misadventures of a thirty-something single woman.\n\n5. **Love Actually (2003)** - Directed by Richard Curtis, this ensemble film features interwoven stories about love and relationships, starring Hugh Grant, Emma Thompson, Liam Neeson, and others.\n\n6. **The Princess Bride (1987)** - A charming, fairy-tale romance mixed with plenty of comedy, starring Cary Elwes and Robin Wright.\n\n7. **Crazy, Stupid, Love (2011)** - A fresh take on the genre with an ensemble cast, including Steve Carell, Ryan Gosling, Julianne Moore, and Emma Stone.\n\n8. **Notting Hill (1999)** - Starring Hugh Grant and Julia Roberts, it tells the story of a humble bookshop owner and a famous actress who fall in love.\n\n9. **You\u2019ve Got Mail (1998)** - Another collaboration between Tom Hanks and Meg Ryan, showcasing the romantic pitfalls and triumphs of the internet age.\n\n10. **The Proposal (2009)** - A funny and heartfelt film starring Sandra Bullock and Ryan Reynolds.\n\nThese films are just a starting point, and there are plenty more out there to enjoy! If you're looking for romantic comedies beyond these classics, you might explore newer releases or lesser-known gems that might suit your preference.",
